\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{d}$
\end_inset

 can obviously be defined similarly, as maps 
\begin_inset Formula $f\{\phi\}$
\end_inset

 from smooth localized functions 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(\vec{x})$
\end_inset

 to numbers.
 Analogous to class, define the distributional gradient 
\begin_inset Formula $\nabla f$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\nabla f\{\phi\}=f\{-\nabla\phi\}$
\end_inset

.
